Don't abort (or freeze) the debuggee when the debugger connection drops abnormally.

ghc-debug-stub's handle_connection() reads requests with Socket::read(), which
throws SocketError (errno-based) on a read *error* -- i.e. an abnormal client
disconnect: the debugger crashed/OOM'd, or a forwarded (ssh/socat) socket
dropped mid-snapshot. handle_connection only wraps handle_command() in
`try { ... } catch (Parser::EndOfInput)`, and the top-of-loop sock.read() calls
are outside any try, so a SocketError propagates out of handle_connection ->
start_over_un -> no handler -> std::terminate -> abort. That takes the entire
cardano-node down (observed: abort via Socket::read in the node's core dump).

Worse, the snapshot path pauses the process (pause_mutator -> rts_pause, sets
the file-scope `paused` flag). If the debugger dies *while paused*, no resume
command ever arrives, so even catching the error leaves the node frozen
(stop-the-world) forever (observed: container Up but node not logging). So the
catch must also resume_mutator() when paused.

A *clean* EOF returns 0 and is already handled; this only adds the missing
error path: wrap the loop in `try { ... } catch (const SocketError&)`, resume
the RTS if we were paused, then drop the connection. start_over_un's accept
loop serves the next debugger and the node stays up and running.

--- a/cbits/stub.cpp
+++ b/cbits/stub.cpp
@@ -712,6 +712,10 @@
 static void handle_connection(const unsigned int sock_fd) {
     Socket sock(sock_fd);
     char *buf = new char[MAX_CMD_SIZE];
+    // SocketError from the sock.read() calls below (abnormal client disconnect)
+    // would otherwise propagate uncaught -> std::terminate -> abort the node.
+    // Catch it below; if paused mid-snapshot, resume so the node isn't frozen.
+    try {
     while (true) {
         trace("handler is waiting for a request\n");
         uint32_t cmdlen_n, cmdlen;
@@ -747,6 +751,13 @@
           delete[] large_buf;
         }
     }
+    } catch (const SocketError&) {
+        // Abnormal debugger disconnect (reset/broken pipe). Resume the RTS if
+        // the snapshot left us paused (else the node stays stop-the-world frozen
+        // forever), then drop the connection. start_over_un's accept loop serves
+        // the next debugger and the node stays up.
+        if (paused) resume_mutator();
+    }
     delete[] buf;
 }
